## Docker Deployment Guide

### What Changed

The Docker workflow is now `.env`-driven:

- all manual deployment values live in the root `.env`
- `.env.example` documents every supported variable
- `scripts/deploy.ps1` can initialize, validate, and run the stack
- MongoDB can run locally with Docker or be switched to Atlas by editing `.env`

### Files You Will Use

- `docker-compose.yml`
- `.env`
- `.env.example`
- `docker/backend.Dockerfile`
- `docker/frontend.Dockerfile`
- `docker/nginx.conf`
- `scripts/deploy.ps1`

### Quick Start

1. Initialize the environment file if needed:

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\deploy.ps1 -Action init
```

2. Edit `.env` and review at least:

- `JWT_SECRET`
- `CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS`
- `MONGODB_URI`
- host ports such as `FRONTEND_HOST_PORT`

3. Start the full stack:

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\deploy.ps1 -Action up
```

4. Check running containers:

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\deploy.ps1 -Action ps
```

### Local MongoDB Mode

The default `.env` enables:

```text
COMPOSE_PROFILES=local-db
```

That starts the bundled `mongodb` container and uses:

```text
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://pharmaadmin:change-me@mongodb:27017/?authSource=admin
```

Use this mode when you want the fewest setup steps on a developer machine or a quick single-host demo deployment.

### MongoDB Atlas or External MongoDB Mode

If you already have MongoDB Atlas or another managed MongoDB instance:

1. Open `.env`
2. Clear `COMPOSE_PROFILES`
3. Replace `MONGODB_URI` with your external connection string
4. Keep or adjust the per-service `*_MONGODB_DATABASE` values

Example:

```text
COMPOSE_PROFILES=
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/?retryWrites=true&w=majority&appName=PharmaERP
```

If one service must use a different cluster, uncomment only that service's `*_MONGODB_URI` variable in `.env`.

### Useful Commands

Start everything:

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\deploy.ps1 -Action up
```

Stop everything:

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\deploy.ps1 -Action down
```

View logs:

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\deploy.ps1 -Action logs
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\deploy.ps1 -Action logs -Service frontend
```

Restart one service:

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\deploy.ps1 -Action restart -Service auth-service
```

Render the final Compose configuration:

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\deploy.ps1 -Action config
```

### Manual Docker Compose Commands

If you prefer raw Docker commands instead of the helper script:

```powershell
docker compose --env-file .env up -d --build
docker compose --env-file .env ps
docker compose --env-file .env logs -f
docker compose --env-file .env down
```

### Application Endpoints

- Frontend: `http://localhost:<FRONTEND_HOST_PORT>`
- Auth health: `http://localhost:<AUTH_SERVICE_HOST_PORT>/api/v1/actuator/health`
- Inventory health: `http://localhost:<INVENTORY_SERVICE_HOST_PORT>/api/v1/actuator/health`
- Finance health: `http://localhost:<FINANCE_BILLING_SERVICE_HOST_PORT>/api/v1/actuator/health`

With the default `.env`, those resolve to:

- `http://localhost:3000`
- `http://localhost:8081/api/v1/actuator/health`
- `http://localhost:8084/api/v1/actuator/health`
- `http://localhost:8090/api/v1/actuator/health`

### Security Notes

- `.env` is ignored by Git and should stay local to each environment
- `.env` is also excluded from the Docker build context
- do not commit Atlas usernames, passwords, or production JWT secrets
- rotate `JWT_SECRET` before any shared or production deployment

### Troubleshooting

| Issue | What To Check |
| --- | --- |
| Backend container exits on startup | `powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\deploy.ps1 -Action logs -Service <service-name>` |
| Frontend loads but cards fail | verify `VITE_*` values in `.env` and check backend health endpoints |
| Mongo connection errors | validate `MONGODB_URI`, `COMPOSE_PROFILES`, and optional `*_MONGODB_URI` overrides |
| Port binding conflict | change the relevant `*_HOST_PORT` value in `.env` |
| Compose file looks wrong after edits | run `powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\deploy.ps1 -Action config` |
